# Operational Mode — SrujanaSangama

> **This is an example template.**
> Copy this file to `context/mode.md` (no `.example` suffix) to activate.
> `context/mode.md` is **gitignored** — it controls agent behaviour locally and must never be committed.

---

## Current Mode

```
mode: production
```

---

## Valid Values

| Value | Effect |
|---|---|
| `production` | **Default.** Agents load only their plugin's `rules/` and `workflows/`. `CONSTITUTION.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and all `specification/` files are **not loaded** and must not be modified. |
| `development` | Agents load `CONSTITUTION.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `specification/` files in full. Spec-driven sprints, task planning, and implementation are permitted. |

---

## How to Switch Modes

**Enable development mode** (to begin a spec sprint):
```bash
# Copy this template to create the live file
copy context\mode.md.example context\mode.md
# Then edit context\mode.md and change the value to:
#   mode: development
```

**Return to production mode** (when sprint is complete and merged):
```bash
# Edit context\mode.md and set:
#   mode: production
# Or simply delete the file — absence defaults to production
```

> [!CAUTION]
> In **production mode**, AI agents must refuse any request to edit, create, or delete files in
> `specification/`, `CONSTITUTION.md`, `AGENTS.md`, or `eval/`.
> Only Sanjay Chitnis (@sanchitnis) may switch the repository to development mode.
